message.content:
1. The mean waiting times (WTs) of CTAS 5 patients decreased.
2. The decrease in mean WTs of CTAS 5 patients was by 28 minutes.
3. The 95% confidence interval (CI) for the decrease in mean WTs of CTAS 5 patients was from 19 minutes to 37 minutes.
4. The decrease in mean WTs of CTAS 5 patients was statistically significant with a P value less than 0.001.
5. The decrease in mean WTs of CTAS 5 patients occurred post FTA.
